    • Field Detail

      • enabled

        private boolean enabled
        This defines whether the plugin is enabled or not. If the plugin is not enabled, breeding will not generate spawn eggs and no debugging will happen when a breeding event occurs.

        The values under the config file can either be "true" or "false" (ignoring case). If the value is missing or set incorrectly, this value defaults to "false".

      • globalChance

        private int globalChance
        This defines the percent chance a spawn egg should spawn instead of a baby, given individualMobChance if the mob is set to "-1".

        The values under the config file should be set as an integer between 0 and 100. If the value is missing or set incorrectly, this value defaults to "0".

      • individualMobChance

        private int[] individualMobChance
        This defines the percent chance a spawn egg should spawn for each individual mob type.

        The values under the config file should be set as an integer between -1 and 100. Setting the value as -1 will automatically use the globalChance value. If the value is missing or set incorrectly, this value defaults to "-1".

      • debugLevel

        private int debugLevel
        This defines whether debug info for the plugin should be outputted, and at what visibility it will be outputted at. It outputs the entire event (cause, context, entity, location, etc.) and reasons why a breeding event failed to create a spawn egg item (prng, wrong type).

        There are 4 options for setting the debug level:

        1. Does not output anything
        2. Outputs at the debug level (visible in the log file)
        3. Outputs at the info level (visible in console as white text)
        4. Outputs at the warn level (visible in console as yellow text)

        If the value is missing or set incorrectly, this value defaults to "0".
